U.S. Third Quarter Business Roundtable CEO Survey

-- B y   K r i s t y   S c h e u b l e
-- 
2011-09-29T14:05:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-29/u-s-third-quarter-business-roundtable-ceo-survey-table-.html
Chief executive officers are less 
optimistic about the  U.S. economy , according to the Business
Roundtable, an association of corporate leaders.  The association’s quarterly economic outlook index fell to
77.6 in the third quarter from 109.9 the previous quarter.
During the next six months 36 percent of CEO’s expect to hire
more U.S. based employees.  Capital spending  is expected to 
increase in 32 percent of firms and 65 percent expect sales to rise.  The Business Roundtable is an association of chief executive 
officers of corporations with a combined workforce of more than 12
million workers in the  United States .  SOURCE: The  Business Roundtable     http://www.businessroundtable.com   To contact the reporter on this story:
Kristy Scheuble in Washington at   kmckeaney@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
